==English==
===Alternative spellings===
* [[crystallize]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈkrɪstəlaɪz/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|crystaliz|es}}

#{{transitive}} To [[cause]] something to [[form]] [[crystal]]s
#* ''I '''crystalized''' the copper sulphate by slowly cooling a saturated solution.''
#{{transitive}} To [[coat]] something with crystals, especially of [[sugar]]
#* ''We '''crystalized''' the fruit by coating in sugar.''
#{{transitive}} To [[give]] something a [[definite]] or [[precise]] [[form]]
#* ''After some thought, I '''crystalized''' my ideas for the paper.''
#{{intransitive}} To [[assume]] a [[crystalline]] form
#* ''The copper sulphate '''crystalized''' from solution.''
#{{intransitive}} To [[take]] a definite form
#* ''My ideas '''crystalised''' overnight.''

